overview: Roman Befikadu plays an intellectual woman (Elleni) who is educated abroad and comes back to Ethiopia to run her father’s leather company. Elleni wants to transfer the orderly and timely work experience that she got abroad onto one of the rural areas in Ethiopia without understanding the culture of the society. The film, focuses on the struggle Elleni is confronted with as she attempts this miscalculated social experiment.
title: Adinas
